race.comment: BORN FLASHY (7) did a great job to score by 6 lengths over today's course and distance last start in a far better run. Taking on a better field but he is good enough to cope. MORNING MIRACLE (5) showed good early muster and fought on to finish second last start over 1609m at Colonial Downs (Turf). Drawn to go forward again. Beautifully placed and is sure to be there at the finish. STELLAR VINO (12) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 5.5 lengths when fifth over 1609m at Churchill Downs three weeks ago. Yet to miss the placings in two starts over this course and distance. Finds a more suitable contest and can find winning form. TAPAKENA (1) was unplaced two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1673m at this track, beaten 11 lengths into seventh. Better than recent efforts suggest.
